<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12091b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12091b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12091b"> 91(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> faultless monster / (Edw FitzG &mdash; )</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">He was content with a poem so long as it was good in the main, without minding those smaller beauties which go to make up perfection &mdash; content with a letter that told of health and goodwill, with very little other news &mdash; and content with a friend who had the average virtues and accomplishments of men, without being <mark>the faultless monster</mark> which the world never saw, but so many are half their lives looking for. <small> Edward FitzGerald, <a name="EFMI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EFMI"><cite title="source">Miscellanies</cite></a> (1900) 52</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Edward FitzGerald (1809-83), a friend of Carlyle, Thackeray and Tennyson. He is most famed as translator of the <cite>Rub&aacute;iy&aacute;t of Omar Khayy&aacute;m</cite>. </mm> </dd></dl>
